"{\n  \"correct\": \"no\",\n  \"explanation\": \"The seaborn scatterplot function does not require a legend by default because it does not plot multiple series of data that would need to be differentiated by a legend. However, if a hue parameter is specified, then a legend would be automatically added. In this case, since there is no hue parameter specified, calling ax.legend() will result in an empty legend being displayed which is unnecessary.\",\n  \"patch\": \"7c7\\n< sbn.scatterplot(data=tips, x='total_bill', y='tip', ax=ax)\\n---\\n> sbn.scatterplot(data=tips, x='total_bill', y='tip', ax=ax)\\n8d8\\n< ax.legend()\\n\"\n}"